Name: AzureHealthInsights
Description: Azure Health Insights provides an API that serves insight models, specific for Health & Life Sciences, that perform analysis and provide inferences to be used by a human.

Enums.Name: DocumentType

Properties.Name: patients
Properties.Description: The list of patients, including their clinical information and data.

Properties.Name: info
Properties.Description: Patient structured information, including demographics and known structured clinical information.

Type.Name: PatientInfo
Type.Description: Patient structured information, including demographics and known structured clinical information.

Properties.Name: sex

Properties.Name: clinicalInfo
Properties.Description: Known clinical information for the patient, structured.

Properties.Description: The clinical coding system, e.g. ICD-10, SNOMED-CT, UMLS.

Properties.Name: code
Properties.Description: The code within the given clinical coding system.

Properties.Name: name

Properties.Name: data

ElementType.Name: PatientDocument
ElementType.Description: A clinical document related to a patient. Document here is in the wide sense - not just a text document (note).

Properties.Name: type
Properties.Description: The type of the patient document, such as 'note' (text document) or 'fhirBundle' (FHIR JSON document).

Properties.Name: clinicalType
Properties.Description: The type of the clinical document.

Properties.Name: id
Properties.Description: A given identifier for the document. Has to be unique across all documents for a single patient.

Properties.Name: language
Properties.Description: A 2 letter ISO 639-1 representation of the language of the document.

Properties.Name: createdDateTime
Properties.Description: The date and time when the document was created.

Properties.Name: content
Properties.Description: The content of the patient document.

Type.Name: DocumentContent
Type.Description: The content of the patient document.

Properties.Name: sourceType
Properties.Description:
The type of the content's source.
In case the source type is 'inline', the content is given as a string (for instance, text).
In case the source type is 'reference', the content is given as a URI.

Properties.Name: value
Properties.Description: The content of the document, given either inline (as a string) or as a reference (URI).

Properties.Name: configuration
Properties.Description: Configuration affecting the Trial Matcher model's inference.

Type.Name: TrialMatcherModelConfiguration
Type.Description: Configuration affecting the Trial Matcher model's inference.

Properties.Name: verbose
Properties.Description: An indication whether the model should produce verbose output.

Properties.Name: includeEvidence
Properties.Description: An indication whether the model's output should include evidence for the inferences.

Properties.Name: clinicalTrials
Properties.Description:
The clinical trials that the patient(s) should be matched to.
The trial selection can be given as a list of custom clinical trials and/or a list of filters to known clinical trial registries. In case both are given, the resulting trial set is a union of the two sets.

Type.Name: ClinicalTrials
Type.Description:
The clinical trials that the patient(s) should be matched to. 
The trial selection can be given as a list of custom clinical trials and/or a list of filters to known clinical trial registries.
In case both are given, the resulting trial set is a union of the two sets.

Properties.Name: customTrials
Properties.Description: A list of clinical trials.

ElementType.Name: ClinicalTrialDetails
ElementType.Description: A description of a clinical trial.

Properties.Name: id
Properties.Description: A given identifier for the clinical trial. Has to be unique within a list of clinical trials.

Properties.Name: eligibilityCriteriaText
Properties.Description: The eligibility criteria of the clinical trial (inclusion and exclusion), given as text.

Properties.Name: demographics
Properties.Description: Demographic criteria for a clinical trial.

Type.Name: ClinicalTrialDemographics
Type.Description: Demographic criteria for a clinical trial.

Properties.Name: acceptedSex
Properties.Description: Indication of the sex of people who may participate in the clinical trial.

Properties.Name: acceptedAgeRange
Properties.Description: A definition of the range of ages accepted by a clinical trial. Contains a minimum age and/or a maximum age.

Type.Name: AcceptedAgeRange
Type.Description: A definition of the range of ages accepted by a clinical trial. Contains a minimum age and/or a maximum age.

Properties.Name: minimumAge
Properties.Description: A person's age, given as a number (value) and a unit (e.g. years, months)

Type.Name: AcceptedAge
Type.Description: A person's age, given as a number (value) and a unit (e.g. years, months)

Properties.Name: unit
Properties.Description: Possible units for a person's age.

Properties.Name: value
Properties.Description: The number of years/months/days that represents the person's age.

Properties.Name: maximumAge
Properties.Description: A person's age, given as a number (value) and a unit (e.g. years, months)

Properties.Name: metadata
Properties.Description: Trial data which is of interest to the potential participant.

Type.Name: ClinicalTrialMetadata
Type.Description: Trial data which is of interest to the potential participant.

Properties.Name: phases
Properties.Description:
Phases which are relevant for the clinical trial.
Each clinical trial can be in a certain phase or in multiple phases.

Properties.Name: studyType
Properties.Description: Possible study types of a clinical trial.

Properties.Name: recruitmentStatus
Properties.Description: Possible recruitment status of a clinical trial.

Properties.Name: conditions
Properties.Description: Medical conditions and their synonyms which are relevant for the clinical trial, given as strings.

Properties.Name: sponsors
Properties.Description: Sponsors/collaborators involved with the trial.

Properties.Name: contacts
Properties.Description: Contact details of the trial administrators, for patients that want to participate in the trial.

Properties.Name: name
Properties.Description: The person's name.

Properties.Name: email
Properties.Description: The person's email.

Properties.Name: phone
Properties.Description: A person's phone number.

Properties.Name: facilities
Properties.Description: Research facilities where the clinical trial is conducted.

ElementType.Name: ClinicalTrialResearchFacility
ElementType.Description: Details of a research facility where a clinical trial is conducted.

Properties.Name: name
Properties.Description: The facility's name.

Properties.Name: city
Properties.Description: City name.

Properties.Name: state
Properties.Description: State name.

Properties.Name: countryOrRegion
Properties.Description: Country/region name.

Properties.Name: registryFilters
Properties.Description:
A list of filters, each one creating a selection of trials from a given
clinical trial registry.

ElementType.Name: ClinicalTrialRegistryFilter
ElementType.Description: A filter defining a subset of clinical trials from a given clinical trial registry (e.g. clinicaltrials.gov).

Properties.Name: conditions
Properties.Description:
Trials with any of the given medical conditions will be included in the selection (provided that other limitations are satisfied).
Leaving this list empty will not limit the medical conditions.

Properties.Name: studyTypes
Properties.Description:
Trials with any of the given study types will be included in the selection (provided that other limitations are satisfied).
Leaving this list empty will not limit the study types.

Properties.Name: recruitmentStatuses
Properties.Description:
Trials with any of the given recruitment statuses will be included in the selection (provided that other limitations are satisfied).
Leaving this list empty will not limit the recruitment statuses.

Properties.Name: sponsors
Properties.Description:
Trials with any of the given sponsors will be included in the selection (provided that other limitations are satisfied).
Leaving this list empty will not limit the sponsors.

Properties.Name: phases
Properties.Description:
Trials with any of the given phases will be included in the selection (provided that other limitations are satisfied).
Leaving this list empty will not limit the phases.

Properties.Name: purposes
Properties.Description:
Trials with any of the given purposes will be included in the selection (provided that other limitations are satisfied).
Leaving this list empty will not limit the purposes.

Properties.Name: ids
Properties.Description:
Trials with any of the given identifiers will be included in the selection (provided that other limitations are satisfied).
Leaving this list empty will not limit the trial identifiers.

Properties.Name: sources
Properties.Description:
Trials with any of the given sources will be included in the selection (provided that other limitations are satisfied).
Leaving this list empty will not limit the sources.

Properties.Name: facilityNames
Properties.Description:
Trials with any of the given facility names will be included in the selection (provided that other limitations are satisfied).
Leaving this list empty will not limit the trial facility names.

Properties.Name: facilityLocations
Properties.Description:
Trials with any of the given facility locations will be included in the selection (provided that other limitations are satisfied).
Leaving this list empty will not limit the trial facility locations.

ElementType.Name: GeographicLocation
ElementType.Description:
A location given as a combination of city, state and country/region. It could specify a city, a state or a country/region.
In case a city is specified, either state +country/region or country/region (for countries/regions where there are no states) should be added.
In case a state is specified (without a city), country/region should be added.

Properties.Name: city
Properties.Description: City name.

Properties.Name: state
Properties.Description: State name.

Properties.Name: countryOrRegion
Properties.Description: Country/region name.

Properties.Name: facilityAreas
Properties.Description:
Trials with any of the given facility area boundaries will be included in the selection (provided that other limitations are satisfied).
Leaving this list empty will not limit the trial facility area boundaries.

ElementType.Name: GeographicArea
ElementType.Description: A geographic area, expressed as a `Circle` geometry represented using a `GeoJSON Feature` (see [GeoJSON spec](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7946)).

Properties.Name: type
Properties.Description: `GeoJSON` type.

Properties.Name: geometry
Properties.Description: `GeoJSON` geometry, representing the area circle's center.

Type.Name: AreaGeometry
Type.Description: `GeoJSON` geometry, representing the area circle's center.

Properties.Name: type
Properties.Description: `GeoJSON` geometry type.

Properties.Name: coordinates
Properties.Description:
Coordinates of the area circle's center, represented according to the `GeoJSON` standard.
This is an array of 2 decimal numbers, longitude and latitude (precisely in this order).

Properties.Name: properties
Properties.Description: `GeoJSON` object properties.

Properties.Name: subType
Properties.Description: `GeoJSON` object sub-type.

Properties.Name: radius
Properties.Description: The radius of the area's circle, in meters.

Properties.Description: An array of errors, if any errors occurred during the processing job.

Properties.Description: An array of details about specific errors that led to this reported error.

Properties.Name: InnerErrorObject
Properties.Description: Inner error.

Operations.Name: matchTrials
Operations.Description: Creates a Trial Matcher job with the given request body.

Parameters.Name: endpoint
Parameters.Description: Supported Cognitive Services endpoints (protocol and hostname, for example: https://westus2.api.cognitive.microsoft.com).

Parameters.Name: repeatabilityRequestId
Parameters.Description: An opaque, globally-unique, client-generated string identifier for the request.

Parameters.Name: repeatabilityFirstSent
Parameters.Description: Specifies the date and time at which the request was first created.

Parameters.Name: TrialMatcherData
Parameters.Description: The body of the Trial Matcher request.

Headers.Name: Operation-Location
Headers.Description: The location for monitoring the operation state.

Headers.Name: Retry-After
Headers.Description: The Retry-After header can indicate how long the client should wait before polling the operation status.

Headers.Name: Repeatability-Result
Headers.Description: Indicates whether the repeatable request was accepted or rejected.
